About this item

  • 2024 Upgraded Bluetooth 5.3 and One-Step Pairing: A97 Bluetooth earphones have the most advanced Bluetooth 5.3 technology, provides faster and more stable signal transmission and successfully achieves low latency without interruption. Once open the lid of charging case, earbuds will automatically connect to the last paired device.
  • Hi-fi Stereo and ENC Noise Cancelling: Our wireless earbuds are equipped with 13mm high-efficiency speakers, which make the bass more punchy and the midrange full and textured, so stereo sounds are crisp, clear, and balanced. 4 built-in ENC noise cancelling mics work together to reject noises around you, keeping your voice sounding clear for every call.
  • Comfortable to Wear: The ergonomic design ensures secure fit and long-lasting comfort, no more sore ears even after extended use, especially for sports. Single ear bud is only 4g easy to pick up, charging case only 29g and can be easily stowed in pocket. Xinwld Bluetooth headphones strive to bring you the best wearing experience.
  • Dual LED Display and 40Hrs Playtime: Wireless headphones use the unique Dual LED display technology to accurately display the remaining power of earbuds and charging case. Bluetooth earbuds playtime lasts for over 6-8 hours from single charge and total 40 hours with charging case. So you don't have to worry about sudden power outage while traveling or going out.
  • IP7 Waterproof and Smart touch control: Wireless earphones using IP7 nano-coating technology, it can protect internal components from liquids and makes them ideal for intense workouts and runs. Earbuds support dual ear touch control, helping to play, pause, adjust volume, answer, end calls, activate siri and google assistant more convenient.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5 out of 5 stars
    Do recommend.
    If youre like me, you bought a pair of fancy high end ear pods when they first became a thing, held onto them for longer than you usually do with such things, and then tragically lost them in some unimaginable way and have been trying to fill the void with cheap replacements ever since because youre certainly not paying 198 for something that can easily just fall out of you pocket or get snapped in half when seized by a 4 year old twice in one life time.What Im trying to say, and if youve made it this far then well done, is that Ive seen my fair share of cheap air pods. So I am confident when I say that these are hands down the best audio quality and comfort Ive seen in this price range so far.Size wise, they are about the shape and size of Apple air pods pro gen 2, so if you like putting them in cases thats roughly what youre looking for.They come in a few different colours, be wary as one vendor was randomly selling the dark blue version for 150, while every other colour was 20, and other than the colour there was no stated difference.They use rubber in ear noise cancellers, there for your mileage may vary with comfort and fit depending on your tolerance for things being proper IN your ear and having the right rubber bit to fit your ear, they include a few different sized rubber bits like most do, the ones that were already on there happened to fit me perfectly, and dont fall out while Im running so take from that what you will.They have a non-intrusive display on the front that tell you numerically how much charge is left, which I for one appreciate over the number of lights system most use, which in my experience tell you the case is fully charged for a week, then drop down to 1 light inexplicably and then are dead 5 minutes later.So in conclusion, going on Holiday and need a cheap set of ear buds? Or need a set to tide you over until you can get a second mortgage approved to replace the set of Beats you dropped down the toilet and couldnt bring yourself to fish out? These are ear buds for you.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Very good
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 13 October 2024
    Colour Name: GreenVerified Purchase
    I recently got my hands on these Wireless Earbuds with Bluetooth 5.3 and Ive been quite impressed, especially considering their price point. Here's what stood out to me:

    Sound Quality & Bass

    The sound quality is excellent, particularly if you're a fan of deep bass. These earbuds deliver crisp highs and rich lows, making them perfect for listening to music, podcasts, or even watching videos. The HiFi Stereo really brings out the details in songs, and the deep bass enhances the overall listening experience. I was surprised by how much power they pack in such a small package.

    Noise-Cancelling Performance

    One of the best features is the ENC (Environmental Noise Cancelling) mics. The earbuds block out a good amount of background noise, which is great for commuting, working in a noisy environment, or even just trying to focus. They wont completely eliminate all noise like high-end over-ear models, but they do a solid job for earbuds, especially when it comes to cutting down on chatter or ambient sounds.

    Battery Life & Charging

    The 40-hour playtime is another strong point. I didnt need to worry about constantly recharging them throughout the day. The dual LED display on the charging case is a nice touch, showing exactly how much charge is left in each earbud and the case itself. Its super convenient, and I found the case to be compact enough to carry in a pocket or bag without any hassle.

    Fit & Comfort

    Comfort is always a concern with in-ear buds, but these fit snugly and stay in place well, even during workouts. The IP7 waterproof rating is an added bonus if you plan to use them during exercise or in wet conditions, so they can handle sweat or light rain without any issues.

    Storm Johnstone
    4.0 out of 5 stars Not perfect, but for the money an amazing buy!
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 8 March 2024
    Colour Name: BlackVerified Purchase
    I picked these up when my previous wireless earbuds took a unscheduled trip through the washing machine... Initially I just needed a cheap replacement with the idea that I'd save for some better ones down the line, but honestly I'm really happy with these so I'm probably not going to bother upgrading from them.

    When I was searching for some replacement earbuds these were suggested by Amazon to me with an RRP of 59.99 and sale price of 19.99 + a 15% discount voucher that I could apply at checkout, so at the end I managed to pay only 16 (!!!) for these wireless earbuds, which is frankly insanely good value!

    Fit and Comfort:
    Honestly they fit me really well, the ear bud section that goes down into the ear canal is oval rather than round, this is the first time I've tried an in-ear earbud that has this shape and its really surprisingly comfortable. Also the tips (presumably silicone?) are extremely thin and soft, which really reduces any pressure on the inside of the ear canal. The rest of the earbud fits snugly inside the ear and the microphone stalk that protrudes down outside the ear is short and low profile so it doesn't get in the way. They are light weight and comfortable for long periods but I don't know how secure they would be for intense workouts. I mainly use them while sat or walking, where I've had no problems.

    Sound:
    I really enjoy the sound of these earbuds. It is bassey but its not overpowering as can be found with a lot of lower-end earbuds. The mids and high tones are represented well and they are reasonably clear. Now they are not going to compete with high end earbuds, but I've certainly paid much more for much worse audio, and not that long ago.

    Noise Cancelling:
    The "noise cancelling" of these earbuds is purely due to their in-ear design. There is no active noise cancelling like you might find on higher end ear buds, but the noise cancelling they offer is quite effective thanks to their fit. Once you start playing music of a podcast they do easily drown out background noise. This comes with all the usual risks involved in being in your own little world, from walking out in front of traffic or seemingly ignoring your girlfriend because you didn't hear her asking you a question - buyer beware! ;)

    I'm not sure how they would fair in truly loud environments. I reach for my Bose Quiet Comfort 35 over-ear headphones with active noise cancelling for things like flights or loud public transport.

    Interface:
    I know why they don't have any physical buttons are purely use a touch sensitive panel on the side of each earbud, because it makes it so much easier to protect against moisture and it's one less thing to wear out. But I have to say the touch interface is a little clunky and is probably one of the weaker points of the product. Adjusting volume has to be done quite slowly because if you tap too quickly it will misread that as a double-tap and then pause whatever you're listening to or even worse hang-up on whoever you're talking to. Also if you've just got one ear-bud in then you only have the option to either just increase or lower the volume as the right earbud is used for volume up and the left earbud is used for volume down. The system does work and I guess it contributes to the light weight of the product as well but its just a little clunky.

    Microphone:
    I've not had people complain about not being able to understand me while I've taken calls on these ear buds. But I have left myself quite a few voice notes using them and I notice the mic quality to not be great. The audio sounds a bit compressed and slightly muddy, specially when compared with the native mic or even the speakerphone mic of my iphone. Its passable, but if audio clarity of the microphone is important to you then you might want to look elsewhere.

    Charging and Battery life:
    I've been getting about 7hrs of battery life so far during my couple of months of use, they charge relatively quickly in the little case and the case does seem to be able to fully charge them at least 3 times. I love the little screen on the front of the case that lets you know the charge state of each earpod and the overall charge state of the case battery as well. Works well and does exactly what it says on the tin. The magnet on the lid of the case is strong and I've had no problems with it popping open unexpectedly. My only negative on the case would be that its outer surface is very slick and slippery. With even slightly greasy hands it can be easy to drop. A matt coating on the outside would be nice, as is often seen on the higher end earbuds.

    Pairing:
    This is the one weak point of these ear-buds. But it does depend on your use-case. I often switch devices, Throughout the day it's not uncommon for me to pair them to my iphone, my work PC, my laptop, my ipad and then my phone again. If you just intend them to be paired to one device then it's really not a problem as once they are paired they connect quickly and seamlessly as soon as you open the lid of the charging case. By the time you have them in your ears you're connected and ready to go. For me, when I want to switch to another device, I often find I have to power cycle them, or put them back in the case, turn the bluetooth off on my previous device (say for instance my phone) and then they will connect to the new device without issue when I get them back out of the case. This is slightly annoying but now I've got used to it, it's not really a problem. My previous wireless ear buds were much higher end and they could be connected to 2 devices at the same time and this made things much more seamless for my use case.

    TLDR = If just using with one device they are great, swapping between devices is annoying.

    Overall:
    I'm not sure I'd spend the RRP of 60 on these, If I was spending that much I'd probably go a little higher and get something from a known brand like Anker, Sony or even Sennheiser. But for the price of a large pizza these things are truly excellent value. If you want to sit and listen to music or podcasts during your commute and not be heartbroken if you lose them or accidentally wash them then I really think you can't go wrong!
